Anonymous Mon 04 Sep 2023 08:07:57 No.59297033 Report
Quoted By: >>59297224 >>59297260
>>59296857
Endtown. It's a webcomic where some sort of event has taken place where everyone exposed mutated, with those awake turning into monsters and those asleep turning into various cartoon-like animal creatures. But there's a small percentage of exposed people who didn't mutate. the Topsiders are unexposed humans, and specifically very interested in eradicating whatever caused the mutations and the mutated alike. There was also a post-apocalyptic war, and pretty much no-one lives on the surface.

It's been years since I read it. It's kind of a wild, weird ride. I'm convinced the author is some flavor of crazy. He used to update every day until it literally gave him health problems. All of the characters come from previous webcomic attempts, which are more like comedic newspaper type strips, and not very funny. But Endtown is bleak as fuck. Good comic until a certain point where a lot of people dropped it, me included. It spawned a bunch of fan comics, too. The most recent being Going Feral, which seems to follow the same mutation rules.

Endtown is both a testament for and an argument against webcomics being the unfiltered vision of the author.
